      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a bit of a \"both sides\" answer, isn't it? But if you really look at the impact, isn't the \"censorship\" side mostly just a way for people to avoid being called out for things that are actually wrong? Like, isn't what people call \"censorship\" usually just accountability for bad behavior?",
