      "content": "i mean \"uncomfortable reality\" is one way to put it, but it feels like it's going way beyond just accountability. when people lose their jobs or get harassed just for having a different political view or questioning certain policies, isn't that actually damaging to democracy? doesn't that make the movement more about control than justice?",
